<refentry id="psld">
  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>psld</refentrytitle>
    <manvolnum>8</manvolnum>
  </refmeta>

  <refnamediv>
    <refname>psld</refname>
    <refpurpose>the &ps; license daemon</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>psld</command>
      <arg>-v?</arg>
      <arg>-f <replaceable>configfile</replaceable></arg>
      <arg>--version</arg>
      <arg>--usage</arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>
    <note>
      <para>
<!--        MOD:  -->
        This program is no longer required for &ps; version 4.1.
      </para>
    </note>
    <para>
      The &ps; license daemon sends so called multicast license pings at
      regular intervals to the &ps; daemons <xref linkend="psid"/>. If a daemon
      is not able to receive these ping for too long, it will suspend work and
      shut down.
    </para>
    <para>
      In order to test if the license daemon is up, the use of <xref
	linkend="mlisten"/> is recommended. Assuming the &ps; cluster contains
      N nodes, the N+1st spinning bar of <xref linkend="mlisten"/> output
      denotes, if the license daemon is running, i.e. if everything is set up
      correctly and the license is valid.
    </para>
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>Options</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <option>-d</option>
	  <option>, --debug</option>
        </term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>Activate the debugging mode. If debugging is enabled, no
	    <citerefentry>
	      <refentrytitle>fork</refentrytitle>
	      <manvolnum>2</manvolnum>
	    </citerefentry> is executed on startup. This is done as default in
	    order to run <command>psld</command> as a daemon process in
	    background. Furthermore the output is much more verbose and not
	    directed to <citerefentry>
	      <refentrytitle>syslog</refentrytitle>
	      <manvolnum>3</manvolnum>
	    </citerefentry> but to stderr. This option implies
	    <option>-v</option>.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <option>-v</option>
	  <option>, --verbose</option>
        </term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>Do more verbose logging.</para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <option>-f</option>
	  <option>, --configfile=<replaceable>file</replaceable></option>
        </term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>Choose <replaceable>file</replaceable> to be the &ps;
	    configuration file. The default is to use
	    <filename>/etc/parastation.conf</filename>.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <option>--version</option>
	</term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>Output version information and exit.</para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <option>-?</option>
	  <option>, --help</option>
        </term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>Show a help message.</para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <option>--usage</option>
	</term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>Display a brief usage message.</para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>See also</title>
    <para>
      <xref linkend="psid"/>, <xref linkend="mlisten"/>
    </para>
  </refsect1>
</refentry>
